         <title mid="49"><![CDATA[A Secret Meeting]]></title>
         <contents mid="50"><![CDATA[<html>Maisa told you to find a rock with special markings in the Red Waste if you want to know the truth. Find the rock with the star pattern and wait until sunset.<BR><BR><FONT color=#086171>Rhadames (Anti-Goddess Faction Secret Passage)</FONT> - <FONT color=#a82424>Red Waste</FONT></html>]]></contents>
         <destination mid="51"><![CDATA[Find the special markings in the Red Waste]]></destination>
         <todo_msg mid="52"><![CDATA[Find the rock with special markings]]></todo_msg>
      </journal>
      <journal index="2">
         <contents_image />
         <destination_pos>1101,n3060</destination_pos>
         <destination_mode>custom:1101@4</destination_mode>
         <statemark_npcid>3060</statemark_npcid>
         <statemark_type>11</statemark_type>
         <trigger_string />
         <maptool_index />
         <title mid="53"><![CDATA[Traces of Old Ties]]></title>
         <contents mid="54"><![CDATA[<html>Someone is waiting in front of the rock with the special markings. It's Lapis, the one who appeared on that wanted poster! Even though Vernicka suspected as much, it's still surprising to see him alive. Talk to Lapis and get some answers.<BR><BR><FONT color=#086171>Rhadames (Anti-Goddess Faction Secret Passage)</FONT> - <FONT color=#a82424>Red Waste(Lapis)</FONT></html>]]></contents>
         <destination mid="55"><![CDATA[Talk to Lapis]]></destination>
         <todo_msg mid="56"><![CDATA[The time has come. Talk to the one who has appeared.]]></todo_msg>
      </journal>
      <journal index="3">
         <contents_image />
         <destination_pos>1101,1,1</destination_pos>
         <destination_mode>custom:1101@4</destination_mode>
         <statemark_npcid />
         <statemark_type>11</statemark_type>
         <trigger_string />
         <maptool_index />
         <title mid="57"><![CDATA[Gathering Wanted Posters]]></title>
         <contents mid="58"><![CDATA[<html>Lapis has asked you to collect the wanted posters for his own safety. It seems he wants to prevent people from learning the content of the posters... Will this prevent people from recognizing him?<BR><BR><FONT color=#086171>Rhadames (Anti-Goddess Faction Secret Passage)</FONT> - <FONT color=#a82424>Red Waste</FONT></html>]]></contents>
         <destination mid="59"><![CDATA[Collect wanted posters in the Red Waste]]></destination>
         <todo_msg mid="60"><![CDATA[Get the wanted posters from the bandits]]></todo_msg>
      </journal>
      <journal index="4">
         <contents_image />
         <destination_pos>1101,n2244</destination_pos>
         <destination_mode>custom:1101@4</destination_mode>
         <statemark_npcid>2244</statemark_npcid>
         <statemark_type>11</statemark_type>
         <trigger_string />
         <maptool_index />
         <title mid="61"><![CDATA[A Place to Hide]]></title>
         <contents mid="62"><![CDATA[<html>The wanted poster has been revised to make the picture look like a completely different person from Lapis. Is he trying to fool the bandits by posting this? I don't know how long it'll work, but... A mission is a mission.<BR><BR><FONT color=#086171>Rhadames (Anti-Goddess Faction Secret Passage)</FONT> - <FONT color=#a82424>Red Waste (Suitable Place)</FONT></html>]]></contents>
         <destination mid="63"><![CDATA[Post the revised wanted poster in a suitable place]]></destination>
         <todo_msg mid="64"><![CDATA[Post revised wanted poster]]></todo_msg>
      </journal>
